<TEXT>
Arsonists tossed firebombs through 
the windows of a bank training centers cafeteria early Tuesday 
and two people were treated for smoke inhalation police said 
Witnesses in the dormitory area of this suburban Frankfurt 
campus complex reported hearing windows smashed and saw four or 
five hooded figures scurry into a wooded area near the Deutsche 
Bank training center at 6 am 
One policeman and a doorman employed by the training center 
suffered from smoke inhalation police said 
None of the 80 bank employees staying at the training center was 
hurt in the attack The damage was limited to the cafeteria and 
classroom area of the center and was estimated at about 588000 
police said 
No one has been arrested and police said there were no known 
motives or claims of responsibility for the attack 
Deutsche Bank AG is West Germanys largest commercial bank 
